(!!WIP!!)

This is a continuation of this shader. This project is intended to be used as a universal sky shader for godot (overcast not supported at the moment). Hope that someone might find it useful in their project)

Implemented features:

    Atmospheric scattering (Nothing changed here from the previous version)
    Sundisc rendering (Again, same as before)
    Stars cubemap rendering at night (Rotated by the sun’s DirectionalLight3D)
    Raymarched moons with spherical texture mapping (controlled by respective DirectionalLight3Ds)
    Raymarched volumetric cumulus clouds (heavy on gpu, but look very fancy ✨)
    Simple and cheap, but somewhat pretty cirrus clouds
    Rainbow 🌈

Refer to this sample godot project to learn about uniforms and settings and how to set up this sky in your project.

This project is still in development so many things work not as intended or don’t work at all)

Also this shader is very unoptimized, so use at your own risk!

Shader created by https://godotshaders.com/author/ansol/
URL: https://godotshaders.com/shader/sky-sorta/
